text: Anita Joy Dow is an Australian politician. She was elected to the Tasmanian House of Assembly for the Labor Party in the Division of Braddon at the 2018 state election. She was Mayor of Burnie from 2014 until 2017, and previously worked as a registered nurse. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:Australian Labor Party members of the Parliament of Tasmania Category:Members of the Tasmanian House of Assembly Category:Women members of the Tasmanian House of Assembly Category:21st-century Australian politicians Category:21st-century Australian women politicians Category:Mayors of places in Tasmania
